HEADWORD: Castorite
<hw>Cas"tor*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[The minerals <ets>castor</ets> and <ets>pollux</ets>
were so named because found <ets>together</ets> on the island of Elba.
See <er>Castor and Pollux</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A variety
of the mineral called petalite, from Elba.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

